Add explicit -channels 1 to each pulse input.

Upstream declares `-channel_layout mono` but omits the matching `-channels 1`.
ffmpeg's pulse demuxer defaults to 2 channels (PipeWire upmixes mono sources
for the client), so the declared layout (1ch) and the negotiated stream (2ch)
disagree and ffmpeg fails to start with exit code 234.

--- a/meet_record/capture.py
+++ b/meet_record/capture.py
@@ -317,6 +317,8 @@
             "1",
             "-f",
             "pulse",
+            "-channels",
+            "1",
             "-channel_layout",
             "mono",
             "-i",
@@ -326,6 +328,8 @@
             "1",
             "-f",
             "pulse",
+            "-channels",
+            "1",
             "-channel_layout",
             "mono",
             "-i",
